cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with the problem of trajectory design of UAVs in a cellular network, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a machine learning framework based on double Q-learning algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of UAVs as flying base stations and the optimization of trajectory design can also be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
